			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">Simple Line Trace Ricochet</span></h1>
			<div id="bodyContent">
				<div id="contentSub"></div>
																<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p><br />
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><div id="toctitle"><h2>Contents</h2></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#Overview"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Overview</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="#Setting_up_the_blueprint"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Setting up the blueprint</span></a></li>
</ul>
</div>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span></h2>
<p>This tutorial will show you how to create a blueprint that will allow the player to shoot a line trace (ray trace) that will ricochet off of surfaces.  More line traces can be strung together to ricochet as many times as needed.
</p><p><br />
To do this you will need to follow this logic:
</p><p>1. On key press, trace a line from the player until an object is hit
</p><p>2. If an object is hit, get the Impact Point and Impact Normal
</p><p>3. Mirror the vector of the original line trace
</p><p>4. Then create another line trace from the Normal and Impact Point
</p>
<div class="thumb tnone"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:942px;"><a href="/File:UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet01.JPG" class="image"><img alt="UPDATE SimpleBlueprintRicochet01.JPG" src="https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/1/10/UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet01.JPG/940px-UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet01.JPG" width="940" height="239" class="thumbimage" srcset="https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/1/10/UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet01.JPG/1410px-UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet01.JPG 1.5x, https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/1/10/UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet01.JPG/1880px-UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet01.JPG 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/File:UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet01.JPG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div></div></div></div> 
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Setting_up_the_blueprint">Setting up the blueprint</span></h2>
<p>1. Open the Character blueprint and go to the Event Graph
</p>
<pre>    a. Right-click and create a <b>Line Trace by Channel</b> node &amp; set the <b>Draw Debug Type</b> to <b>For Duration</b>.
</pre>
<p>2. Getting the player info
</p>
<pre>    a. In the bottom of the <b>MyBlueprint</b> panel, check <b>Show Inherited Variables</b>.
    b. Find the <b>FirstPersonCamera</b> and drag a <b>Get</b> variable into the graph.
    c. Drag off of the camera variable and find the <b>Get World Location</b> node (<b>Context Sensitivity</b> may need to be off).
    d. Plug the return value into the <b>Start</b> pin of the line trace.
    e. Drag off of the camera variable and find the <b>Get Forward Vector</b> node.
    f. Multiply the forward vector by 5000 (or any other value you like, this is the distance the line trace will go).
    g. Add the vectors from the world location and the multiplied value.  Plug the result into the <b>End</b> pin of the line trace.
</pre>
<p>3. Getting the hit infomation and the second line trace
</p>
<pre>    a. Drag off of the <b>Out Hit</b> pin of the line trace &amp; create a <b>Break Hit Result</b> node.
    b. Create another <b>Line Trace by Channel</b> node and set it <b>For Duration</b>.
    c. Drag off of the <b>Normal</b> pin of the break hit and create an <b>Add</b> node.
       (Note: Attempting to reflect 'exactly' off of a normal will sometimes have errors. This adds 1, depending on normal direction, to the next line trace to make sure it is not inside of the object.)
    d. Connect the <b>Impact Point</b> to the <b>Add</b> node and connect the output to the Start pin of the next line trace.
    e. Drag off of the <b>Impact Normal</b> &amp; get a <b>Mirror Vector by Normal</b> node.
    f. Connect the added result of the player info to the <b>In Vect</b> pin.
    g. Connect the <b>Impact Normal</b> pin of the break hit to the <b>In Normal</b> pin of the mirror vector.
    h. Connect the return value of the mirror vector to the End pin of the line trace.
</pre>
<p>4. Stringing more line traces together
</p>
<pre>    a. Select the last 3 nodes (<b>Break Hit Result</b>, <b>Mirror Vector by Normal</b>, and <b>Line Trace by Channel</b>).
    b. Copy them to the end of the blueprint.
</pre>
<div class="thumb tnone"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:942px;"><a href="/File:UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet02.JPG" class="image"><img alt="UPDATE SimpleBlueprintRicochet02.JPG" src="https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/9/9d/UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet02.JPG/940px-UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet02.JPG" width="940" height="331" class="thumbimage" srcset="https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/9/9d/UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet02.JPG/1410px-UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet02.JPG 1.5x, https://d26ilriwvtzlb.cloudfront.net/9/9d/UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet02.JPG 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/File:UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet02.JPG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div></div></div></div> 
<pre>    c. Connect the <b>Execute</b> pins for the line traces.
    d. Connect the <b>Out Hit</b> pin to the new <b>Break Hit Result</b>.
    e. Connect the <b>Return Value</b> of the mirror vector to the new <b>Mirror Vector by Normal</b>
    f. Repeat this as many times as needed to have the line trace continue to ricochet.
</pre>
<div class="thumb tnone"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:942px;"><a href="/File:UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet03.JPG" class="image"><img alt="UPDATE SimpleBlueprintRicochet03.JPG" src="https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/b/bf/UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet03.JPG/940px-UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet03.JPG" width="940" height="330" class="thumbimage" srcset="https://d3ar1piqh1oeli.cloudfront.net/b/bf/UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet03.JPG/1410px-UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet03.JPG 1.5x, https://d26ilriwvtzlb.cloudfront.net/b/bf/UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet03.JPG 2x" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/File:UPDATE_SimpleBlueprintRicochet03.JPG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div></div></div></div> 
<p><br />
<b>NOTE:</b> <i>This tutorial has been tested and works correctly with version 4.6.1 of the editor.</i>
</p><p>Cheers,
</p><p>TJ Ballard
</p>
